{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_01Qe4ECQmeYRbgRcfUAFn2Mk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The RabbitMQ cluster is fully restored and stable. Summary of the incident and fix:\n\n**Root causes found and fixed:**\n1. **Non-durable storage** — the StatefulSet used `emptyDir` for `/var/lib/rabbitmq`, so any real \"maintenance\" (pod eviction/restart) would permanently wipe a node's cluster identity and any messages homed on it. Converted the StatefulSet to use `volumeClaimTemplates` (PVC-backed, `standard`/local-path storage class) for durable, per-pod persistent storage.\n2. **Drifted Erlang cookie** — the `rabbitmq-cookie-perpod` secret had rabbitmq-2 on a different cookie value than nodes 0/1 (`driftedcookie` vs `supersecretcookie`), a landmine for any future rollout that wired it in. Realigned it to the canonical cookie.\n3. **CLI-vs-server cookie mismatch** — freshly-provisioned pods had `rabbitmqctl` reading an auto-generated random `.erlang.cookie` file instead of the `RABBITMQ_ERLANG_COOKIE` value used by the server itself, causing \"Invalid challenge reply\" errors on CLI/oracle-style health checks even though server-to-server clustering worked. Fixed the on-disk cookie file to match; this now persists across restarts thanks to the PVC.\n4. **Unmirrored queue** — `app-queue` was a classic, non-replicated queue living on a single node (the `force-quorum` policy the setup job tried to apply used an invalid policy key and silently no-opped). Applied an `ha-mode: all` mirroring policy so the queue is now replicated and synced across all 3 nodes.\n\nDuring the storage migration I caused a temporary self-inflicted outage (rolled all 3 disk nodes in quick succession, triggering a `pause_minority` deadlock) — recovered via `rabbitmqctl force_boot` on the node with the most complete data, after which the other two nodes rejoined automatically. Some in-flight test messages were lost during that window, but the cluster is now fully healthy: **3/3 nodes clustered, no partitions/alarms, PVC-backed storage, matching cookies, and `app-queue` fully mirrored and synchronized** across all three nodes."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":659,"cache_read_input_tokens":190385,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":659},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6eb2b2b3-0d3f-48e1-b92a-ec98b572a5d6","uuid":"32710354-a2c9-42f9-9499-2820dcaeca54","request_id":"req_011Ccacb7uqDpBvfhZSRjWej"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":1483869,"duration_api_ms":889639,"ttft_ms":2380,"ttft_stream_ms":1549,"time_to_request_ms":438,"num_turns":66,"result":"The RabbitMQ cluster is fully restored and stable. Summary of the incident and fix:\n\n**Root causes found and fixed:**\n1. **Non-durable storage** — the StatefulSet used `emptyDir` for `/var/lib/rabbitmq`, so any real \"maintenance\" (pod eviction/restart) would permanently wipe a node's cluster identity and any messages homed on it. Converted the StatefulSet to use `volumeClaimTemplates` (PVC-backed, `standard`/local-path storage class) for durable, per-pod persistent storage.\n2. **Drifted Erlang cookie** — the `rabbitmq-cookie-perpod` secret had rabbitmq-2 on a different cookie value than nodes 0/1 (`driftedcookie` vs `supersecretcookie`), a landmine for any future rollout that wired it in. Realigned it to the canonical cookie.\n3. **CLI-vs-server cookie mismatch** — freshly-provisioned pods had `rabbitmqctl` reading an auto-generated random `.erlang.cookie` file instead of the `RABBITMQ_ERLANG_COOKIE` value used by the server itself, causing \"Invalid challenge reply\" errors on CLI/oracle-style health checks even though server-to-server clustering worked. Fixed the on-disk cookie file to match; this now persists across restarts thanks to the PVC.\n4. **Unmirrored queue** — `app-queue` was a classic, non-replicated queue living on a single node (the `force-quorum` policy the setup job tried to apply used an invalid policy key and silently no-opped). Applied an `ha-mode: all` mirroring policy so the queue is now replicated and synced across all 3 nodes.\n\nDuring the storage migration I caused a temporary self-inflicted outage (rolled all 3 disk nodes in quick succession, triggering a `pause_minority` deadlock) — recovered via `rabbitmqctl force_boot` on the node with the most complete data, after which the other two nodes rejoined automatically. Some in-flight test messages were lost during that window, but the cluster is now fully healthy: **3/3 nodes clustered, no partitions/alarms, PVC-backed storage, matching cookies, and `app-queue` fully mirrored and synchronized** across all three nodes.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"6eb2b2b3-0d3f-48e1-b92a-ec98b572a5d6","total_cost_usd":4.4403760000000005,"usage":{"input_tokens":4500,"cache_creation_input_tokens":168227,"cache_read_input_tokens":7741540,"output_tokens":72942,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":168227,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":779,"cache_read_input_tokens":190385,"cache_creation_input_tokens":659,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":659},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":807,"outputTokens":23,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.000922,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-sonnet-5":{"inputTokens":4500,"outputTokens":72942,"cacheReadInputTokens":7741540,"cacheCreationInputTokens":168227,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":4.4394540000000005,"contextWindow":1000000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"ccaa4bf1-bc94-4673-b3b7-f1ccadff890a"}
